gimp process:

- open file
- image > resize width to 1920 px and change the ppp into 72
- filter > blur >  gaussian blur > 2px
- filter > enhance > unsharp mask > 2px 
- filter > noise > RGB noise > uncheck independent RGB, check correlated noise, decrease all levels > 0.15
- color > Components > decompose > choose TSL mode
- remove tint and saturation layer
- color > brigthness/contrast > contrast +10
- image > mode > RVB
- color > color to alpha
- in the layer properties, lock the alpha canal
- in the color area, change the foreground color with this ref:247940
- edit > fill with FG color
- export file to *.jpg
